cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY

This paper deals with the analysis of language and concepts on the World-Wide Web, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of weights and meaning bounds to represent concepts is also related to machine learning (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper's focus on identifying problem situations and effects on the web suggests a connection to data mining and analysis (cs.LG) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
